			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pet HP has never been any real problem.. What hurt mages before this spring was the awful damage mitigation of the pets. The only real uses for pet HP outside of the old pet canni is when you've got a cleric and can CH the pet, and when you're simply chaining pets. Then again, the AA "elemental durability" is broken for that too since the pet gets summoned at the base HP and has to regen to full, which it won't because it will see action immediately. I don't think that the mages that get the new pet foci of today solo/group that much either, since you've seen just about all of Norrath and have just about all important AA's. Which means that the increased mana regen won't be used for faster XP. 
<br />

<br />
The point is that even today, it wouldn't matter that much if I was still running around with a 4k HP pet, since the mage heals are absolute numbers anyway, not CH's, and high HP won't slow down their HP's dropping. A small use in that the chance of enrage on high-hitting mobs is greater.
<br />

<br />
I'd gladly have pets with only base unfocused HP if I could have necromancer mana regen. I must say it made the game less interesting for me too, since now playing a mage in XP groups is just sending pet to attack, using your malosinia clicky and casting the same nuke over and over, with no variation possible or any way to contribute more. And of course more downtime soloing - is that something you consider making the game more interesting?<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=597626">Enharjaren Fenrirsbane</a> Arch convoker
<br />
Arch Overseers(applicant for now)
<br />
Bristlebane</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
