			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok. Let me see if I have this straight. 'Cause I just gotta be missing something here...
<br />
<ul><li> In a particular scenario,
<br />
<li> Wherein the mob queue pipeline is being kept fully stocked by other players,
<br />
<li> With short breaks between each mob,
<br />
<li> The Magician class,
<br />
<li> Which consists solely of offensive capabilities,
<br />
<li> Over a period of time,
<br />
<li> Can outdamage the Wizard class,
<br />
<li> Who, in addition to offensive capabilities,
<br />
<li> Offer groups ROOT, SNARE, BUFS, and PORTS.</ul>Okay. A few questions:
<br />

<br />
1) What am I missing here? What is it that the Magician class brings to a party? Cause on the surface, it looks like Wizards have them beat hands down.
<br />

<br />

<br />
2) How much is "a lot"? How badly were Magicians outdamaging Wizards in this particular (stocked pipeline) scenario?
<br />

<br />
Was it 10-to-1? 2-to-1? 1.5-to-1?
<br />

<br />

<br />
3) How fast was PetCanni permitting folks to recover full mana?
<br />

<br />
1 Minute. Less? 5 Minutes?
<br />

<br />

<br />
4) How long did it take before Magicians started to outdamage Wizards?
<br />

<br />
It looks like your Magician casts two spells for every nuke the Wizard casts, just to do equivalent damage. Plus there's petcanni time... During all of which the Wizard is medding.
<br />

<br />
Just how long does the pipeline need to run before Wizards go OOM, and Magicians start outdamaging them?
<br />

<br />
Won't breaks between mobs, as opposed to solid chain-pulling, extend that timeline by giving Wizards extra med time between each mob death?
<br />

<br />

<br />
5) When it existed, what percentage of mana was returned by petcanni? At early levels (44), it would take a fair bit of time to recover full mana. I had the impression that, as one advanced, petcanni improved. Allowing one to regain full mana in somewhat less time.
<br />

<br />
If that's true, wouldn't it have made more sense for petcanni to have its mana capped. So that, regardless of level, it would have taken several minutes to recover full mana?
<br />

<br />
As in something like 8 minutes for the Wizard to med to full mana, vs 3-5 for petcanni.
<br />

<br />
Or am I out in left field here...
<br />

<br />
-Rusty.
<br />

<br />

<br />
